TestOutputAskWithJsonHintMaterializesOnFirstAccess
/ output.ask + (json) hint: the variable holds the raw string until
/ first property access, which triggers JSON deserialization via the
/ Serializers registry. Mock the ask so the test doesn't block on an
/ interactive channel; the mock returns a JSON literal string.
- mock.intercept pattern="output.ask", return='{"foo":42}', write to %m%
- ask "give me json", write to %a%(json)
- assert.equals expected=42, actual=%a.foo%
